<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="85" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Acalypha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Acalypha marginata" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">Acalypha marginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was treated by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4117969" author="Coode, MJE" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" pagination="39 - 48" refId="B16" refString="Coode, MJE, 1979. Notes on Euphorbiaceae in the Mascarene Islands: II. Kew Bulletin 34 (1): 39 - 48, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4117969" title="Notes on Euphorbiaceae in the Mascarene Islands: II." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4117969" volume="34" year="1979">Coode (1979)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authority="subsp. marginata" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="A." infraspecific-rank="subsp." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. integrifolia" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" rank="species" species="integrifolia" subspecies="marginata">A. integrifolia subsp. marginata</taxonomicName>
. We consider 
<taxonomicName family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. marginata" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">A. marginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a distinct species, differentiated mainly by its variegated leaf blades and vestigial female bracts that are not accrescent in fruit vs. non variegated leaf blades and conspicuous female bracts that are accrescent in fruit in 
<taxonomicName family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. integrifolia" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" rank="species" species="integrifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">A. integrifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We include as synonyms 
<taxonomicName authority="subsp. panduriformis" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="A." infraspecific-rank="subsp." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. integrifolia" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" rank="species" species="integrifolia" subspecies="panduriformis">A. integrifolia subsp. panduriformis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="A." infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. integrifolia var. crateriana" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" rank="variety" species="integrifolia" variety="crateriana">A. integrifolia var. crateriana</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="A." infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. integrifolia var. saltuum" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" rank="variety" species="integrifolia" variety="saltuum">A. integrifolia var. saltuum</taxonomicName>
because they have the same characters as 
<taxonomicName family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. marginata" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">A. marginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
